  &lt;p id="FvyLAG"&gt;Leica is &lt;a href="https://leica-camera.com/en-US/photography/70-years-leica-m"&gt;celebrating the 70th anniversary&lt;/a&gt; of the M rangefinder camera, but the most precious gift it’s giving for the occasion is for only 250 rich people and costs $22,995. The ludicrously expensive &lt;a href="https://leica-camera.com/en-US/photography/cameras/m/m-edition-70"&gt;Leica M Edition 70&lt;/a&gt; set includes a platinum-plated Leica M-A 35mm film camera with Leicavit fast winder, a matching 50mm APO-Summicron-M f/2 lens, and a metallic film container with a roll of black-and-white film. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="f2vJhi"&gt;Yes, the film container is also platinum, and yes, that’s completely ridiculous.&lt;/p&gt;
